The Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) has repeated its demand for land expropriation without compensation as the country marks Heritage Day. The EFF says in a statement that the land is a core element of African heritage. The party has also reiterated calls for Cape Town International Airport to be renamed after Winnie Madikizela-Mandela and for East London’s airport to be named after Black Consciousness movement leader, Steve Biko. The EFF further wants ‘Die Stem’ dropped from the National Anthem. Click below to read the statement: 